1 H.41
2 An act relating to abuse of the dead body of a person
3 The Senate proposes to the House to amend the bill by striking out all after
4 the enacting clause and inserting in lieu thereof the following:
5 Sec. 1. 13 V.S.A. § 3761a is added to read:
6 § 3761a. ABUSE OF THE DEAD BODY OF A PERSON
7 (a) No person shall, knowingly without legal authorization, intentionally
8 burn, mutilate, disfigure, dismember, or destroy the dead body of a person.
9 (b) No person shall violate subsection (a) of this section for the purpose of
10 concealing a crime or avoiding apprehension, prosecution, or conviction of a
11 crime.
12 (c) No person shall commit sexual conduct upon the dead body of a person.
13 (d)(1) A person who violates subsection (a) of this section shall be
14 imprisoned not more than five years or fined not more than $5,000.00, or both.
15 (2) A person who violates subsection (b) or (c) of this section shall be
16 imprisoned not more than 15 years or fined not more than $10,000.00, or both.
17 (e) As used in this section:
18 (1) “Dead body of a person” does not include the cremated remains of a
19 person.
20 (2) “Sexual conduct” means any of the following committed against the
21 dead body of a person:
